Don’t Overpay for Technology Again
Investors weren’t wrong; they just paid too much to be right.
That’s the lesson of the Nasdaq Composite Index’s 15-year slog to surpass the high of 5048.62 that it first set on March 10, 2000. Before you get too excited over the booming stock market and Thursday’s new Nasdaq record, make sure you aren’t repeating the mistakes of the past.